  "text": "Kerrie mentions being \"respectful of life\", it is not for her to terminate. She accepts the inevitability of death but how she can still care. She identifies those dying as \"very vulnerable people\" and fears a precedent if death is hastened. Kerrie clearly draws on the slippery slope argument [CITATION_1] . Similarly, and although patient suffering is a prime consideration for Gary (Palliative Specialist), it does not override his fundamental belief that control over the timing of death should not rest solely with him:",
